	 (2000000082,2000000031,'I am an adult patient with recurring abdominal pain, bloating, and nausea. I have had these symptoms for several years and have been to multiple doctors, but no one can seem to diagnose the root cause. I would like to have a comprehensive examination done by Doctor Robertson to better understand my symptoms and possibly discover any underlying health issues.','2023-03-31 12:00:00'),
	 (2000000088,2000000031,'I am a XY-year-old patient, and I recently experienced abdominal pain and bloating. It started after a small meal and has been going on for a few days now. I am also experiencing nausea and indigestion. I would like Dr. Robertson''s advice on whether these symptoms could be related to a more serious condition or if they are normal post-meal symptoms.','2023-03-06 12:00:00'),
	 (2000000084,2000000032,'As an adult patient, I am concerned about the persistent redness and scaling on my face that has been bothering me for the past few months. It''s been difficult to ignore, and I''d like to discuss possible underlying causes and treatment options with Dr. Reed.','2023-02-07 12:00:00'),
	 (2000000085,2000000032,'As an adult patient, I am seeking consultation with Dr. Reed as I have developed an unusual rash on my skin. It has been persistent for the past few weeks, and I am quite concerned about it. The rash is red, scaly, and itchy, and it appears to be spreading rapidly. I am not sure whether this is a serious condition or not, and I would like Dr. Reed''s professional opinion on this matter.','2023-04-10 14:00:00'),
	 (2000000087,2000000032,'Hello Doctor Reed, I am an adult patient and I am experiencing some changes in my skin, primarily on my forehead and upper lip. I am concerned because I have heard that these areas can be indicative of more serious health issues. Could you please examine these areas and provide any necessary recommendations or treatment options? Thank you.','2023-04-06 13:00:00'),
	 (2000000083,2000000033,'Hi Doctor Holland, I''m a 30-year-old adult patient seeking your advice regarding persistent abdominal pain and bloating. I recently completed a half-marathon but have been experiencing discomfort ever since. Could it be dehydration or something more serious?','2023-08-10 13:00:00');
